<TITLE> Support CSR in farming, SME sectors: Atiur to banks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh Bank governor Atiur Rahman has asked banks and other financial institutions to consider streaming funds to encourage corporate social responsibility (CSR) activities in productive sectors like agriculture and small and medium enterprises. At the launch of the three-day 'Bank and Non-Bank Financial Institution Fair-2009' at Hotel Sheraton on Thursday, the central bank also urged them to work harder to earn greater customer confidence and consolidate financial bases, as well. On the fair, he said such expositions should help promote the role of the financial institutions. Twenty-five government and private banks and non-banking financial institutions have taken part in the fair showcasing and offering services and service-related information. Rihen Pervege, a Prime Bank sales executive, said their stall offered a lot of banking merchandises. A client can apply for bank loans in the fair, he added. Bangladesh Association of Banks chairman Kazi Mahmud Sattar, Bangladesh Insurance Association chairman Rafiqul Islam and Bangladesh Leasing and Finance Company Association president AKM Rafiqul Islam were present at the inaugural ceremony. The fair is open to public from 10am to 4 pm at its venue. b
